SIMPLE: famish
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Famish
<hw>Fam"ish</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Famished</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Famishing</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[OE. <ets>famen</ets>;
cf. OF. <ets>afamer</ets>, L. <ets>fames</ets>. See <er>Famine</er>, and
cf. <er>Affamish</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To starve, kill, or
destroy with hunger.</def> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To exhaust the strength or endurance of, by hunger;
to distress with hanger.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>And when all the land of Egypt was <qex>famished</qex>, the people
cried to Pharaoh for bread.</q> <rj><qau>Cen. xli. 55.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The pains of <qex>famished</qex> Tantalus he'll feel.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To kill, or to cause to suffer extremity, by
deprivation or denial of anything necessary.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>And <qex>famish</qex> him of breath, if not of bread.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>To force or constrain by famine.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He had <qex>famished</qex> Paris into a surrender.</q>
<rj><qau>Burke.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Famish</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Famish
<hw>Fam"ish</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To die of hunger; to
starve.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To suffer extreme hunger or thirst, so as to be
exhausted in strength, or to come near to perish.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>You are all resolved rather to die than to <qex>famish</qex>?</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To suffer extremity from deprivation of anything
essential or necessary.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The Lord will not suffer the soul of the righteous to
<qex>famish</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Prov. x. 3.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Famishment</ent>⟦br⟧
